This paper deals with metadata anonymization, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The project also involves the development of a toolkit (MAT) for metadata anonymization, which could fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses privacy policies and balancing information loss with privacy enhancement, which could be relevant to the field of cyber law and policy (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions future possible works, which suggests that the project involves software engineering (cs.SE).
